reviews.text: great breakfast sandwiches! everything is made in house
Rustic spot with great breakfast on amazing site made breads. We always leave with an extra loaf or two for later. Good coffee too!
Must stop here.   Best bread anywhere.   Every item executed perfectly.   Wish I could take this restaurant home with me.
This place is so good! We went for breakfast and were very satisfied. Didn’t have crazy diner size portions and it was quality food. Also got sandwiches to go for lunch and they were just as good!

Enjoyed a fabulous breakfast! All five of our party tried something different and loved it. The real maple syrup was a nice touch. The farm fresh eggs were delicious. The kids books were fun to read while waiting for our food.

I have never had a WORSE restaurant experience in my life!!!  (And just for background, I'm 47, eat out a lot, and worked both as a waitress and bartender while going to college and graduate school.)

Last Saturday (2/23/13,) four of us arrived at the Cowboy at about 7:45 pm.  There were no available tables, so we decided to take a seat at the bar.  I ordered an “oat martini.”  (I didn’t have the drink menu in front of me, but had had the drink there a couple of weeks before).  The bartender said “I’ve worked here since we opened, and we’ve NEVER served ANY alcohol made from oats.”  (The emphasis was hers.)

I was flustered, because, as I said, I had had the drink there a couple of weeks before; so I ordered “the basil drink.”  As the bartender began making “the basil drink,” I looked at the menu.  There at the bottom of the list was the “High West Martini” made with, you guessed it, oat vodka.  [From the High West Distillery website: “The heart of Vodka 7000” comes from our favorite grain, oats….That’s why we’ve created Vodka 7000’, the only vodka in the world that’s made from oats.”]  

I called over to the bartender saying “Here it is on the menu, the “oat martini.”  She brought over “the basil drink”, set it in front of me and said, “Here’s YOUR BASIL drink!”  (Again, the emphasis was hers.)  I said “I want the “oat martini.”

Then things got weird.  She said “Next time you order the drink, say I want the High West Martini.  In fact, I’m going to have them re-print the menu and remove the words “oat” altogether.” 

Well here’s where she made a HUGE mistake – she assumed I’d come back - AND I NEVER WILL.  

I paid for the drink – and left immediately!!!
Awesome food. Fantastic service. Eat the Vietnamese meatballs.
Decent food.  Confusing decor.  Horribly, insultingly overpriced.  $16 hamburger overpriced.  $9 glass of house wine.   I'd pass by....
great atmosphere, cutting edge drinks, wonderful unique food - same owners of carribean cowboy that is now closed

We had a great dinner here the other night. The restaurant was busy but we were able to get seated pretty quickly at a high top in the bar. The food was hot, plentiful and delicious, especially those french fries! I liked the unique menu items as well as the colorful and extensive cocktail menu and can't wait to go back to try a few new things. Definitely check out Lisa G's!

Places off the main drag in Lake Placid seem to try harder - better food, more realistic prices, better service, etc.. Lisa Gs checks all those. Interesting dishes done well. We had a variety of items from across the menu - lentil salad, goat cheese salad, steak, fish, ice cream sandwich - all very good. Will be back hopefully in summer to enjoy the riverside patio.
Stopped in for drinks, and they were amazing! Had the Salty Ricardo- so yummy! Bar Staff was extremely nice. We definitely felt welcomed!
Omg! Everything is so delicious! From daily soup to the fresh fish, and the cheesecake is a must! If we ever make it back through lake placid again we'll be sure to stop by here again!
Oh, I liked this place. Really delicious cuisine and wonderful, warm service. There's many good places to eat in Lake Placid, and Lisa's is among the best.
Great night at Nicola's. Got to spend time with Mike Nicola, the owner.   Good food, good service, we'll definitely be back...!

Worst restaurant experience I have ever had. First, the waiter just forgot about me, even though I was the only customer in the restaurant, and I had to go looking for him to get a refill on my Coke. Before I left he asked if there was anything else he could bring me, and I said he could bring me a little more Coke. I thought he was being nice until the bill arrived and I saw they had charged me $9 for Cokes. I was livid. I asked the ditzy blonde at the bar, and she just said so sorry, there's nothing we can do. Soon the owner came out and was also unapoligetic. He called me cheap and an a--hole!!! If I could give this place minus five stars, I would. 

Owner's self-righteous response is ridiculous.  By the way, the three Cokes you served equated to about one Coke because of all the ice and the small glasses. And the only restaurants I've ever been to that charge for refills are in Lake Placid. I've been traveling to Estes Park, Colo. annually for 22 years and have spent thousands of dollars there. I was hoping I'd love Lake Placid the same way, but my experience with rude New Yorkers like you convinced me never to return. Nice job

We ordered take out last week and i was very impressed with the quality of the (freshly made) pasta and pizza.The woman who took our order (the wife of the chef) was extremely friendly and accommodating, and I found the food to be traditionally prepared, which I prefer (Italian-Italian - not American-Italian cuisine). The flavor combinations were absolutely perfect.  My children loved it as well.

All of our pasta was luke warm...in temperature and flavour. We got the spaghetti with meatballs, broccoli rabe and chicken penne, salmon special, and the sausage con verde pasta. The salt and pepper shakers were used by everyone at the table because flavour was really lacking. There was also no fresh ground pepper or parmesan. Service was also slow; we only got bread when we asked for it and then it was then served with dinner but they took our bread plates away! It's okay though, we didn't eat the bread because it was stale. Overall, very disappointed and underwhelming.

Decidedly meh.  They claim to be Mediterranean but are really Italian.  I ordered the lasagna special that I sent back; it was made to days earlier (I asked), had very little filling, was burned to the plate, and had rubbery noodles.  They replaced it with chicken Parmesan that was very average.

Generally overpriced.  I'll be surprised if it is still there the next time I'm in Lake Placid.

I love this place! We camp at the Meadowbrook Campground right behind here when we come up to hike and I've been to eat here twice. On Friday's and Saturday's they have live music and everyone really enjoys themselves. The food is great BBQ and good portions. It's a really cool atmosphere, you can either sit inside, outside under a canopy or on picnic tables in front of the stage. The staff is always friendly and the service is great, too. I always talk about this place and mention it to anyone going up to Saranac Lake/Lake Placid area.

Fun...outdoor, picnic style seating (there are a few booths) with live music when we were there. Busy, but we were able to seat right away. Nice assortment if beers and full bar in a cool hut. No ribs when we were there...something about a process change...bummer. I'd say a little overpriced for what you are getting in portion size. I think they are counting on the fact it is a high tourist pass-through. Play area for kids keeps them entertained. Be careful leaving, hard to see traffic on busy road! I'd give it another shot to try the ribs...

Tail O’ The Pup was a great experience! Jody was an amazing server. She was on point with everything between grabbing drinks bringing kids foods out & letting us know what was going on. She was very friendly and made our total experience even better. The food is very well priced and delicious! The portions are insane! A definite must have experience while visiting.

Tail O’ the pup is a “must try” restaurant in Lake Placid. It’s only 8 minutes away from Mirror lake and the best part that it has an outdoor seating area where you can eat and chill. Their menu offers a wide variety of food and their sea food section is what attracts people the most to go and try. Me and my husband ordered “to go” a Hot Lobster roll and a Cold Lobster roll. Maybe those two dishes sounds pretty much the same but definitely taste different. The Hot Lobster Roll is a lobster sandwich marinated only with butter and served hot and The cold Lobster Roll is a cold lobster sandwich with mayo, lettuce and celery. Both platters were served with French Fries and potato salad. Their food tasted like Heaven and they were both yummy and flavorful. Unfortunately, their service is a bit slow but Be patient Guys because it’s definitely worth it!!

After a lengthy hike my wife and I stopped tired and hungry for some takeout.  I walked up and a rather harried waitress took my order and returned with my food about 20 minutes later.  I have no complaints!  The brisket and pulled pork were particularly excellent and the sides staple and nothing special.  The dining area looked a bit like a madhouse but was packed with people which might make me do a takeout order.  I’d go back again someday.

Nice atmosphere. Their wings and pizza are fantastic. We ate in one night and did take out for another night during our week's stay. We'll worth it. If you're in the area, you'll want to check it out!

Good prices for Lake Placid.  The food is delicious, and there’s always tons of seating, so a wait is never really an issue!  If you’re staying at the Golden Arrow, the location of Generations doesn’t get much closer...

Met a friend at Generations for breakfast. Had the Venison Hash with poached eggs and rye toast. Delicious! My friend had blueberry pancakes equally delicious! Mary our waitress was wonderful and attentive when needed. Price was perfect. Quiet for a Sunday Morning. Very nice all around.

Went in just before new year's and service was horrible actually it was pretty no. Existent.  Enough that my wife and myself were sitting people watching and we saw more people complaining to each other and getting up and leaving than ever.  Why sit people if your not going to serve them.  Never will we stop foot in here again

Always fun! Highly recommended by me.
Happy New Year's!
Excellent proper pub with great view over bay. Ever changing choice of ales and great gins. Very friendly staff, good food and best place in Falmouth to watch  live sport
Great classic pub with great local food amazing food and comfy vibe. I'd highly recommend it.

We came here as part of o 25 strong group For dinner .we were all asked to arrive promptly as our pre ordered food would be served for 7pm sharp.Unfortunately not the case.the mains came out in twos and threes,some of us had finished eating before others had received theirs.!!
The food itself was Ok but have had better for the price!. Beer drinkers also beware ,the range of draft beers is light on well knowns .I tried a couple of pints of their real ales but wasn’t bowled over.After spending nearly £80 There I won’t be in a hurry to return,Need to do better.
Its got some good ales a unique outside sitting area with fantastic views

A very nice, traditional pub.
The view across the Penryn to Flushing and across the Carrick Roads is stunning, especially in the evening as the sun sets.

We just came back from fours days, had a Lunch ans a Dinner at the Brown Dog. They were the best meals of the week.  We met the owners and they are great people, the service was out standing and the experience was unbelievable.

If you are in town you have to stop by, can not say one bad thing.

Even our Bull Dog (Bella Rosa) loved the dinner outside.

The food and the view were really exceptional!  There were two servers for the dining room, and unfortunately we got the not very friendly one who was stingy with the wine pour, but she did not ruin our great experience!  Try to the scallops Rockefeller.

Wow! What a gem! The service, the presentation, the view... all spectacular
 But the food? Out of this world. The Baja burger was flavorful and cooked just right. And the thanksgiving panini would be worth driving back from PA for over and over!

This restaurant would not seat us........Why???? I guess because I was wearing a black leather jacket.  Plenty of tables were available.  I would never go back to a place that judges their clientele,  and then decides if they want to serve you or not. I did not have that problem with anyother restaurant in Lake Placid. Shame on them.

We visited in the summer after hiking up Cascade, wanting a view of the lake for lunch. I had the lobster bisque and my fiancé had the steak sandwich. We both left unhappy with the quality of the food. The lobster bisque was more of a gravy base than a tomato base.. Coming from boston this was just unexpected?? And we also thought the steak in the sandwich was tough. We wouldn't go back even for the view.

Bob, JP, Joe, and the rest of the staff made our stay so lovely, want to thank all of you because we didn't get a chance to do it in person. The room here was very nice, thank you to the cleaning staff that took care of it each day while we were out. The chef here has some incredible stuff on the menu all of the food we had was truly delicious. We hope to be coming back here because it was all wonderful, thank you all again.
-Kevin
I got the veal saltibocca and it was a delight. Out server was very helpful and the restaurant is gorgeous inside and out.
Incredible breakfast, beautiful touches on the decor made the whole place really warm, cosy and inviting!! The owners were fantastic and really friendly. Will definitely be back.

As a summer resident I have always enjoyed my visits here! Last night was such a great experience, the staff was friendly, the service was great and the chef sure knows what he is doing! That you for a fun night and great meal! THE LOBSTER ROLL IS INCREDIBLE!!!!
Great food. Wonderful service.  Pleasant atmosphere.  Fireplace was giving off warm heat.
Awesome food. Great for kids and very healthy. Gives you gas so don't eat a lot.
Loved the views from here. Beautiful lake. There are benches to sit and enjoy. Kayaks are available to rent. There is also beach.

Sit outside if you can; the views of Mirror Lake are beautiful. The food is wonderful. Our party of six enjoyed everything immensely. The staff was phenomenal. Just the perfect place for a memorable evening in Lake Placid.
Good food, great service, nice place, cold in winter so dress warm

The amazing view from the deck looks ng out over mirror lake at sunset  set the tone.  Though somewhat casual, the service and food was far superior to a much more upscale restaurant we ate at last week for a celebration ration.  Complaints are just nits. One person's medium rare blackened stake with Brandy sauce was closer to medium.  I highly recommend the boathouse.

I sent my husband and daughter here for a special ski trip. They liked the lodge itself, though the service was average, and had a nice time but when they came home I saw that they were billed more than was agreed to. I had called several times to get a confirmation after I made the reservation and was told their system was down. When I called to try work it out after the stay I was told the manager would call me in a few hours. Then someone else called and said, without listening, that I was wrong and she was right. (I see on another recent review someone also had a tough time with the same person  and her dismissive approach). I asked again to speak to the manager and emailed him twice. It has been several days and he seems to have no interest in calling or responding which is very disappointing. I respect people are busy but a quick I got your email and will get back to you would have been nice or a simple conversation would have been helpful. This was our first experience with Whiteface Lodge and this total disregard from management negatively impacted our perception. I hate to think if they cannot address minor stuff what happens when it is a big issue? Too bad because the place was nice.

An incredible resort with great food and service.  The gas fireplace worked like a charm and made the living room nice and warm.  The restaurants were beautiful.  There is an ice skating rink, pool, hot tubs and spa.  We had a wonderful time both at the resort and in town.  About 20 minutes from Whiteface Mountain.  Definitely coming back.

Top notch resort. This was our first time visiting The Whiteface Lodge. We were automatically upgraded to a two bedroom suite. The resort is beautiful, staff was very friendly, breakfast in the morning is free and the selection and quality of the food was outstanding. We will definitely be going back !
Friendly staff. Very clean. Spacious. Good food. Lots of things to do. Pool and spa are excellent. Excellent place for families. Live music was top notch.

My wife and I went here for our honeymoon, glad we did! They treated us great! There offered to upgrade our room to a beautiful 3 bedroom suite! The amnities are also great! The complimentary breakfast far exceeded our expectations which makes sense since really the whole experience did.
